What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Tocilizumab Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Tocilizumab is a humanized IgG1 monoclonal antibody used for the treatment of cytokine release syndrome (CRS), systemic juvenile idiopathic arthritis (sJIA), giant cell arteritis (GCA), and rheumatoid arthritis (RA). It works by blocking the binding of IL-6.

The market drivers include the increasing geriatric population, rise in the prevalence of autoimmune and inflammatory conditions, growing concentration of major pharmaceutical companies. Growing government initiatives and rising awareness are the factors that will expand the global tocilizumab market. Rising R&D activities, clinical trials, and growing medical research will provide beneficial opportunities for the global tocilizumab market in the forecast period. Tocilizumab increase the cholesterol level, which affects liver function test. It also shows some side effects such as hypercholesterolemia, high blood pressure, mouth ulcers, allergic reactions, dizziness, upper respiratory tract infections, and other severe conditions. All these factors hamper the market growth and will further challenge the global tocilizumab market in the forecast period mentioned above.

The product type segment is dominating the global tocilizumab market due to the rise in patient population and tocilizumab is approved for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and systemic juvenile idiopathic arthritis. These factors are further stimulated the market growth.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the tocilizumab market, valued at USD 72.37 million in 2022, will reach USD 181.75 million by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 12.20% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030. The market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team includes in-depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework.

